<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="169" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[809,1441,589,992]" pageId="4" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis box="[810,906,589,610]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="169">Remarks.</emphasis>
Unfortunately the material is meagre and infertile and the permanently mounted specimens poorly displayed. The species is remarkable for the shallowness of the hydrotheca which provides minimal support for the hydranth. There is indication of desmocytes above the diaphragm but the interior of most hydrothecae is obscured by tissue and adventitious material. There is an indication of incipient anastomosing of the ultimate branches.
</paragraph>
